Hello Luke,
&nbsp;
Got it — Royal Mail Rates for international and EU customers only, hidden for UK orders. That is exactly what the automation rules are designed for.
&nbsp;
Based on the screenshots you shared, you have already found the right option: Royal Mail Rates (the one marked NEW in the app). This uses the public rate card, requires no API credentials, and does not include label generation — which matches your setup perfectly.
&nbsp;
Once you have connected Royal Mail Rates, here are the specific steps to restrict it to non-UK destinations:
&nbsp;
  In the app, go to Settings → Shipping Rates → Rate Automation.  Create a new rule and set the condition to Zone != United Kingdom.  Set the action with Add Carrier Services by selecting Royal Mail Rates for orders matching that condition.  &nbsp;
This means Royal Mail services will appear at checkout for your EU and international customers while remaining hidden for UK orders, where your existing UK rates will continue to show as normal.
&nbsp;
If you need any help configuring the automation rule or run into anything unexpected during setup, please let us know and we will assist right away.
&nbsp;
Thanks and regards,
Manohar V
Team PluginHive

